commit.message:
logrotate.8: address mandoc lints

Fix the following two mandoc lints:

    mandoc: logrotate.8:13:2: ERROR: skipping unknown macro: .\}
    mandoc: logrotate.8:79:83: STYLE: input text line longer than 80 bytes: will exit with value...

Skip compressing skipped copy

Skip compressing the non existent file skipped during truncation under a
rotate count of 0.

Closes: #552

Do not skip copy when mailing

Do not skip copying the about to truncated file if the rotate count is 0
when the log content should be mailed.

test: use UTC timezone for date calculations

Using a local timezone with DST might result in a date returned twice,
see #569.

Call tzset(3) to always initialize time conversion information

localtime_r(3) is not required to initialize the time conversion
information like localtime(3) does.
Drop unnecessary localtime(3) mktime(3) roundtrip

Stretch systemd timer over one hour

The initial introduction of the systemd timer in commit 05228c2f ("Add
logrotate service and timer for systemd") included the directive
`AccuracySec=12h`.  AccuracySec= is not a load distribution option but a
power saving one, see systemd-timer(5).  In commit 3f3991ee ("Timer
unit: change trigger fuzz from 12h to 1h") the value was reduced to 1h,
while the discussion in #230 also mentioned load distribution.

Use RandomizedDelaySec= instead of AccuracySec= to actually spread the
start time of the service, and ignore potential system wakeups below the
rate of the default of AccuracySec= of one minute.

Fixes: #567

Support quoted arguments in readModeUidGid()

Support quoted user and group names in readModeUidGid(), which supports
names incorporating whitespaces.

Fixes: #105

Rewrite readModeUidGid()

Restore old behavior when one or two arguments are specified for the
create and createolddir directives.  This was broken with the
introduction of numeric uid/gid support.

Fixes: #561
test: add create syntax regression

Use madvise(2) correctly

madvise(2) does only support one advice at a time, not multiple or'ed
together, see the kernel implementation or their non-bitmask values.

Call madvise(2) for each advice individually.

Drop the advise of MADV_DONTFORK, since logrotate is single-threaded
and during the lifetime of the mapping no child is forked off.

Currently the usage of MADV_SEQUENTIAL (=2), MADV_WILLNEED (=3) and
MADV_DONTFORK (=10) results in MADV_DOFORK (=11).
